-- Former ECB Member Orphanides Says He’ll Teach at MIT Sloan
-- B y   S t e l i o s   O r p h a n i d e s
-- 2012-06-15T13:43:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-15/former-ecb-member-orphanides-says-he-ll-teach-at-mit-sloan.html
Former European Central Bank council
member Athanasios Orphanides said he will begin teaching at MIT
Sloan School of Management later this year.  The former governor of the Central Bank of Cyprus, whose
term expired in April, will be teaching “macroeconomics,
central banking and the European financial crisis,” he said in
an interview today. The school is based in Cambridge,
 Massachusetts .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stelios Orphanides in Nicosia at 
